'''Abominable''', ''[[adjective (part of speech)|adjective]]'' [F. ''abominable''. L. ''abominalis''. See [[Abominate]].]

<ol>
<li>Worthy of, or causing, [[abhorrence]], as a thing of evil omen; [[odious]] in the [[utmost]] degree; very [[hateful]]; [[detestable]]; [[loathsome]]; [[execrable]].

<li> Excessive; large; -- used as an [[intensive]]. [Obs.]

